columns.name: gispropnum
columns.description: Unique identification number for each park property, identified by borough/county (B = Brooklyn M = Manhattan Q = Queens R = Richmond (Staten Island) X = Bronx) and followed by a number.

columns.name: omppropid
columns.description: Unique identification number for a property or portion of a property. In some cases – a standalone, smaller park for example – this number will be equivalent to the GIS Property Number. In other cases – a zone, playground or other site within a larger park – an additional designation of letters and/or numbers will be added.

columns.name: gisobjid
columns.description: Unique identifier that links the property being serviced to an asset in AMPS.

columns.name: route_id
columns.description: Unique identification number for the route as part of which the indicated activity was performed

columns.name: off_route
columns.description: An indicator as to whether or not a property is included on the selected route.

columns.name: description
columns.description: The name of the entire site as it appears on the signs located on the exterior of the park.

columns.name: district
columns.description: The name of the Park Maintenance District in which the property is located.

columns.name: sector
columns.description: Unique identification string of the Park Maintenance Sector in which the property is located.

columns.name: sector_name
columns.description: The name of the sector in which the property is located.

columns.name: sector_desc
columns.description: The numbers of the Park Maintenance Districts that comprise the associated Sector

columns.name: vehicle_number
columns.description: The vehicle number used for the given date and route.

columns.name: date_worked
columns.description: The date on which the indicated activity was performed.

columns.name: start_time
columns.description: The date and time at which the indicated activity started.

columns.name: end_time
columns.description: The date and time at indicated which the activity ended.

columns.name: activity
columns.description: The type of activity captured for a record. Cleaning is indicated by the "Work" activity, while other activity codes are used for other actions.

columns.name: animal_waste
columns.description: An indicator as to whether or not animal waste was cleaned during a visit.

columns.name: broken_glass
columns.description: An indicator as to whether or not broken glass was cleaned during a visit.

columns.name: dumping
columns.description: An indicator as to whether or not dumping was cleaned during a visit.

columns.name: graffiti
columns.description: An indicator as to whether or not graffiti was cleaned during a visit.

columns.name: medical_waste
columns.description: An indicator as to whether or not medical waste was cleaned during a visit.

columns.name: napsw
columns.description: A count of the number of staff in the Associate Park Service Worker title on the cleaning crew during the indicated activity.

columns.name: ncpw
columns.description: A count of the number of staff in the City Park Worker title on the cleaning crew during the indicated activity.

columns.name: ncsa
columns.description: A count of the number of staff in the City Seasonal Aide title on the cleaning crew during the indicated activity.

columns.name: npop
columns.description: A count of the number of staff in the Job Training Participant title on the cleaning crew during the indicated activity.

columns.name: nnpw
columns.description: A count of the number of non-Parks employees on the cleaning crew during the indicated activity.

columns.name: ncrew
columns.description: A count of the total number of workers on the cleaning crew during the indicated activity.

columns.name: fixed_post
columns.description: An indicator as to whether or not an entry was made using the "Fixed Post" module of the application.

columns.name: nhours
columns.description: A count of the adjusted number of hours a given task was performed.

columns.name: daily_task_id
columns.description: A unique ID assigned to each Daily Task entry.

columns.name: daily_task_activity_id
columns.description: A unique ID assigned to each Daily Task activity entry.

columns.name: overlap_flag
columns.description: An indicator as to whether or not the number of hours (nhours) were adjusted for overlapping times and tasks.

columns.name: fiscal_day
columns.description: The relative day of the fiscal year.

columns.name: fiscal_week
columns.description: The relative week of the fiscal year.

columns.name: fiscal_qtr
columns.description: The fiscal year followed by the fiscal quarter for a given record.

view.description:
This data contains cleaning records for City property under the jurisdiction of or maintained by NYC Parks. It includes records of tasks such as opening parks, cleaning and restocking comfort stations, and removing graffiti, litter and natural debris.

For the User Guide, please follow this link
